    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11837090,
      "reputation" : 4813,
      "user_id" : 8662085,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1837fad53736838b219aff68fd874a63?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "DeanM",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8662085/deanm"
    },
    "is_accepted" : true,
    "score" : 444,
    "last_activity_date" : 1535281030,
    "last_edit_date" : 1535281030,
    "creation_date" : 1506194643,
    "answer_id" : 46383454,
    "question_id" : 46280859,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Select the project, then File > ProjectStructure > ProjectSettings > Modules -> sources\nYou probably have the Language Level set at 9:</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/nRRA1.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/nRRA1.png\" alt=\"screenshot\"></a></p>\n\n<p>Just change it to 8 (or whatever you need) and you're set to go.</p>\n\n<p>Also, check the same Language Level settings mentioned above, under Project Settings > Project</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/x6Ub0.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/x6Ub0.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11130508,
      "reputation" : 349,
      "user_id" : 8587147,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://graph.facebook.com/484557228548130/picture?type=large",
      "display_name" : "Dmitry Kaltovich",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8587147/dmitry-kaltovich"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 24,
    "last_activity_date" : 1511813075,
    "creation_date" : 1511813075,
    "answer_id" : 47518948,
    "question_id" : 46280859,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I have had the same problem. There is an answer:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>1.<strong>CTRL + ALT + SHIFT + S</strong>;\n\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>Then go to \"<strong>Modules\"</strong>;</li>\n<li>\"<strong>Dependencies</strong>;</li>\n<li>Change \"<strong>Module SDK</strong>\".</li>\n</ol></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Got it!\nNow u have Java 9!</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1608256,
      "reputation" : 1197,
      "user_id" : 1487868,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/93b5710462ac9c36192bde09a727f5d7?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "felvhage",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1487868/felvhage"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1526028555,
    "creation_date" : 1526028555,
    "answer_id" : 50288497,
    "question_id" : 46280859,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Alternatively via Project Settings:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Project Settings</li>\n<li>Project</li>\n<li>Project language Level (set to fit your needs)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Depending on how your build is set up, this may be the way to go.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 5104728,
        "reputation" : 482,
        "user_id" : 5009319,
        "user_type" : "registered",
