    "last_activity_date" : 1545392766,
    "creation_date" : 1545392766,
    "answer_id" : 53884274,
    "question_id" : 46280859,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>For anyone struggling with this issue who tried DeanM's solution but to no avail, there's something else worth checking, which is the version of the JDK you have configured for your project. What I'm trying to say is that if you have configured JDK 8u191 (for example) for your project, but have the language level set to anything higher than 8, you're gonna get this error.</p>\n\n<p>In this case, it's probably better to ask whoever's in charge of the project, which version of the JDK would be preferable to compile the sources.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2362196,
      "reputation" : 29,
      "user_id" : 2068657,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a51872e847a82f246cd4e28e94a4fcad?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "amitsahu86",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2068657/amitsahu86"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1546937353,
    "creation_date" : 1546937353,
    "answer_id" : 54088154,
    "question_id" : 46280859,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I also had the same problem in IntellijIdea, after selecting the project, then File > ProjectStructure > ProjectSettings > Modules -> sources the option was showing - the Language Level set at 9:</p>\n\n<p>So, I Just change it to 8. Still my issue didn't got resolve.</p>\n\n<p>The main issue was with pom.xml. I reimported the pom.xml file and my issue got resolved.</p>\n\n<p>So, whenever you changed the pom.xml file, IDEA needs to update the project structure. For example if you've added there some more dependencies, IDEA needs to add them as project libraries.</p>\n\n<p>In \"Settings > Build, Execution, Deployment > Build Tools > Maven > Importing\" you can choose \"Import Maven projects automatically\". This will automatically invoke \"Reimport\" action when the pom.xml is changed.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/l4JIL.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">enter image description here</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4055813,
      "reputation" : 1582,
      "user_id" : 3333878,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 38,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/15f47cc6617b300e8e05d0b6c481034d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "abitcode",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3333878/abitcode"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1552370518,
    "creation_date" : 1552370518,
    "answer_id" : 55115039,
    "question_id" : 46280859,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>When using maven project.</p>\n\n<p>check pom.xml file</p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;properties&gt;\n    &lt;project.build.sourceEncoding&gt;UTF-8&lt;/project.build.sourceEncoding&gt;\n    &lt;project.reporting.outputEncoding&gt;UTF-8&lt;/project.reporting.outputEncoding&gt;\n    &lt;java.version&gt;9&lt;/java.version&gt;\n&lt;/properties&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>if you have jdk 8 installed in your machine,\nchange <code>java.version</code> property from <code>9</code> to <code>8</code> </p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 5416397,
