    "creation_date" : 1697435364,
    "answer_id" : 77299610,
    "question_id" : 46280859,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>While setting <code>Language level</code> do note that <strong>various language levels are split across <code>LTS Versions</code> and <code>Other Versions</code> headers</strong>. I missed that and spent a while figuring why level 8 wasn't showing up in my dropdown</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/axPBg.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/axPBg.png\" alt=\"IntelliJ Language level dropdown\" /></a></p>\n<p>Ref: <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/77299629/3679900\">What is Project Language level in IntelliJ IDEA?</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 29954168,
      "reputation" : 11,
      "user_id" : 22955464,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLyApk54wYpYGU-4LDi2bbQt7x2gEte1laoPf1m-ZFx=k-s256",
      "display_name" : "Ibrahim Payak",
